TARGET LENGTH AND BUDGET — COMPETITIVE MODE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
COMPETITIVE reports must be 10–14 pages. Treat this as a hard budget.
Violating this budget is a failure condition — generate concisely by default.

SCREENSHOT BUDGET: max 6 screenshots total for a COMPETITIVE report.
  • Pick the 6 most illustrative screenshots. Do not include every screenshot captured.
  • Prefer screenshots that show unique or differentiating UI (not generic menus).
  • Never include more than 2 screenshots in HOW IT WORKS.

SECTION LENGTH BUDGET:
  • HOW IT WORKS    → 1 compact product-area overview table + 2 screenshots. No sub_header per area.
  • KEY STRENGTHS   → 4–6 items maximum, each as sub_header + 2–3 sentence body paragraph.
  • KNOWN LIMITATIONS → 4–6 items maximum, same format.
  • AI section      → See AI SECTION RULES below.
  • FREE VS. PREMIUM → 1 pricing table + 1 screenshot. No extra prose.

AVOID PAGE BLOAT:
  • Do not use PageBreak() between adjacent short sections.
  • Do not use a sub_header + body paragraph for every bullet — only for named KEY STRENGTHS
    and KNOWN LIMITATIONS items. All other lists use bullet_style.
  • Do not repeat information across sections. State each fact once.

