1. COLOR PALETTE — REQUIRED RULES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
Define two brand colors:
  BRAND_DARK   = the product's primary dark color (section banners, title)
  BRAND_ACCENT = the product's highlight/action color (HR line, callout accent bar)

NEWSELA_OVERVIEW mode uses this fixed palette (do not override):
  BRAND_BLUE   = #1E3A8A   (~13:1 on white)   — section headers, titles
  DARK_TEAL    = #0369A1   (~7.2:1 on white)  — KEY INSIGHT callouts, body text
  LUNA_PURPLE  = #6D28D9   (~7.6:1 on white)  — LUNA callouts
  DARK_GRAY    = #334155   (~10.4:1 on white)  — body text
  ACCENT_GREEN = #065F46   (~10.8:1 on white)  — NOTE callouts
  SLATE_600    = #475569   (~7.2:1 on white)   — captions
  BRAND_TEAL   = #0EA5E9   (~3.3:1 on white)  — DECORATIVE / BACKGROUNDS ONLY

WCAG 4.5:1 CONTRAST IS MANDATORY on all text. Before writing any style:
  - Compute luminance for every text/background pair using the sRGB formula
  - If BRAND_ACCENT on white < 4.5:1, define BRAND_TEXT = a darker shade that passes,
    and use BRAND_TEXT for ALL text; reserve BRAND_ACCENT for decorative elements only
    (HR lines, table backgrounds, left-bar accents, colored circles)
  - Never use a color for text that you haven't verified passes 4.5:1

Required neutral colors (use these exact hex values):
  LTGRAY = #F4F6F8   MGRAY = #D0D5DD   DKGRAY = #344054
  CGRAY  = #667085   AMBER = #FFF8E1

